Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 04:31:06 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Trust ledger: honest grounding for every seed-key algorithm
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add algoProvenance.js — single source of truth for how much each algorithm /
writer can be trusted (bench-verified / grounded-extracted / unverified;
default unverified for unknowns). Attach a grounding record to every ALGOS
entry and correct the overstated hint strings: 'VILLAIN confirmed' (TIPM
mixing is reconstructed, only the tables were extracted), 'VILLAIN q2/q3/q4'
(constants are real but the sxor application is inference), and the cda6 /
sbec / xtea_sgw labels. No algorithm changes — provenance honesty only.

Verified: 43/43 algorithms carry a grounding entry (0 bench-verified, 21
extracted-unconfirmed, 22 unverified); algos.js imports clean.
